<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>It seems that there's a bug in Zend_Translate_Adapter. More specific in the constructor.</p>

<p>When instantiating a Zend_Translate_Adapter without giving $locale argument, value from Zend_Registry::get('Zend_Locale') should be used. 
Appararently it is used in addTranslation() (line 107) method, but then in setLocale() (line 108) the locale field is overwritten.</p>

<p>The bug is in line 108 and could be fixed by replacing:
$this-&gt;setLocale($locale);</p>

<p>With:
if(!is_null($locale)) $this-&gt;setLocale($locale);</p>

<p>I'm passing Zend_Registry::get('Zend_Locale') to the constructor to work around the problem.</p>

